Advertisement. Mexican food has a unique taste, which is a blend of the Native American and Spanish food. Mexico is famous for its chili, which makes this cuisine spicy. More than 140 varieties of chili are grown in Mexico and are included in the Mexican cuisine.amales: These are fiesta foods in Mexico and they belong to the Aztec cuisine. They are made from corn and slaked lime. Slaked lime is also known as nixtamal, which softens the corn for easy digestion. Usually, tamales in Mexico city are wrapped in corn husks.
